      {
        "paragraph_index": 7,
        "text": "Chemically, most “violations” of Irving–Williams are usually **apparent rather than fundamental**: they often arise from comparing non-equivalent equilibria or from ligand-specific structural effects rather than a true failure of the underlying trend.",
